This dog recently arrived and is just settling in.  If you are interested in adopting, you MUST come in person during adoption hours and fill out an application.  Adoption hours and address are viewable on the website at www.smallmiraclesrescue.org


---FAQ---

Is This Dog Currently Available?... This dog is available at the Small Miracles rescue facility in Ellicott City.  To submit an application, please come meet this dog in person.  You can bring your application with you, or you can fill one out when you come in.  Dogs will be removed from PetFinder only when they have an approved application or more than three (3) interested applicants.

Where did this dog come from?...  We rescue dogs from 100% kill shelters in West Virginia and on occasion from Kentucky.  On rare occasions we accept owner surrenders.  Due to the nature of the shelters they were rescued from, we often do not know the dogs' history.

How Old is this dog?...  We look at a dogs' teeth to estimate its age, and then the age is reevaluated by our veterinary staff when the dog is spayed/neutered.  If an age is not posted online, please feel free to inquire.

Is this dog Good With Kids?...  We occasionally know for sure if a dog is good with kids because it came from a home with kids.  This is rare.  We always suggest you bring your children in to meet the dog if you are seriously interested in adopting.  Dogs may like some kids and may dislike others.  Dogs are individuals, just like kids are.

Is this dog Housebroken?...  Advice from a veterinarian:  Even if a dog is housebroken at my house, it does not mean that it understands not to pee at someone else's house.  It ONLY understands not to pee at my house.  Some dogs make the connection that they should only pee outside.  Some must be retrained when they come home.  All we can tell you for sure is whether/or not a dog's crate is clean when we come to walk them in the AM.  All this means is that they are crate trained and waited to pee until we took them outside.

What is this dog's Temperament?...  We do not have a clear picture of a dog's temperament until we have allowed them to settle in for a few days.  Even then they are living in a shelter environment with many other dogs and a lot of daily activity.  It can be difficult to say a dog is "calm" or "nervous" when the shelter environment is playing a big role in that behavior.  We only rescue FRIENDLY dogs who have no known bite history.  If a dog is at Small Miracles, it likes people and has a good temperament.  We always suggest you meet the dog to see if it is the right fit for your lifestyle. 

What are your Fees?...  Base adoption fee is $325 for adult dogs and puppies.  To this, we add a $30 microchip fee, which we register for you, and a 6 month supply of heartworm preventative.  Heartworm preventative costs $40-60 depending on the weight of the dog.  This means that a large dog will total $405.00 and an extra large dog will total $415.00.

Why can't I adopt a FREE dog?...  Our adoption fee covers many procedures which cost much more for us then the amount we ask for from you. We spay/neuter all pets, and we give them their first round of vaccines (canine distemper, bordatella, Rabies if age appropriate).  At a typical vet clinic this would cost you $500 at minimum for the surgery, and each vaccine is roughly $35 each.  Even if your adopted dog does not have all of its shots due to the mandatory waiting period between booster shots, we offer vaccinations at the low cost of $20/shot.  We test all dogs for heartworm disease and tickborn illnesses such as Lymes.  We never euthanize a heartworm positive dog, and treatment routinely costs us $3000/dog.  We collect a fecal sample from every rescued dog and run a microscopic parasite test.  Any parasites found will be treated with two rounds of the appropriate dewormer.  We treat all dogs for fleas and ticks with Advantage.  If a dog has significant dental disease or "very dirty teeth", we will perform a dental cleaning when the dog has its spay/neuter surgery.  A dental cleaning with extractions would cost you upwards of $400-600 at your local vet clinic.

ALSO NOTE... Small Miracle is a 501(c)(3) charitable organization.  We survive off of our adoption fees and donations from the community.  We are a non-profit animal rescue and do not receive income from tax revenue as some county shelters do. 

For more information including Adoption Hours and Rescue Address, please visit our website at www.smallmiraclesrescue.org

Kiera was rescued with her dog friend, Damien, a few weeks ago. They are local dogs, and their owner passed away a year ago. The landlord has been caring for them, and finally reached out for help. That’s how they got to us. Our vet thinks Kiera is 5 years of age. She’s got a lot of spunk. She does walk with a limp in her back leg- but it does not slow her down. Our vet took x rays and said she has an old knee fracture that appears to have healed without medical intervention, hence the limp. He stated he does not recommend surgery, but just management with medication. Kiera is still Mischievous like a puppy- leave treats out and she’s helping herself! So her foster mom does crate her when she leaves, otherwise she gets into things.

Meet Bubba! This very friendly two year old American Pit Bull is as friendly and social as his name sounds. Through no fault of his own, Bubba was about to be dumped by a a very irresponsible owner, when a Good Samaritan stepped up to help him. He is such fun to be around and does extremely well with other dogs and and kids. He is potty and kennel trained, and like most of his breed, he is a big cuddle bug. Bubba is a medium dog and weighs around 50 pounds. He can walk on a leash, but does need some work with heeling. However, Bubba is smart and wants to please, so with a little practice and patience, he will make a good walking companion. Bubba can easily jump a chain link, so he is going to need a home with a six food wooden fence. If you would like to meet Bubba, please contact wendee@sterlingtile.net

I would ideally need to go through a training course with my new adopters so I can blossom into a well behaved giant. I am a beautiful girl with lots to learn and would love a home of my own. ****PETronus Rescue endeavors to include all pertinent information for each of the dogs within our organization with regard to approximate age, potty training status, kennel training status, temperament, activity level, dog/cat friendliness, etc in an effort to give those considering adopting as much information as we have.  Inquiries requesting additional information will not be returned, due to limited volunteers. Thank you for your understanding **** 

Hi there. 

My name is Laila, but I sometimes go by Silly Girl or Goofball. I am a 2-year-old Terrier mix looking for my soul mate. My foster mom says I am super smart, energetic and a love bug. I call myself fun-loving, but I don’t mind being a couch potato at times. 

I even know a few tricks; don’t worry I will teach them to you. I am not looking for much just someone that will take me on walks, plays with me (I love toys) and doesn’t mind when I want to snuggle. My favorite past time is to pay tug of war with your socks and running off with them to shake the monsters out, but don’t worry I will give them back to you as soon as I am done. I don’t mind cats, but I am not a fan of other dogs because I want you all to myself.

—————————————

All PETronus Rescue dogs receive basic vaccinations (distemper/parvo, bordetella, & rabies), spay/ neuter, and microchip prior to adoption. We also treat any know medical issues, including heartworms.

Our dogs live in foster homes while they wait patiently for their forever families to find them. This is beneficial in that they learn house manners, crate training, housebreaking, etc while they wait and we are also able to get a very realistic picture of their energy level, temperament, etc so that we can place them in a home that is the best fit.

Our adoption fees are $200 for dogs over 1 year of age and $250 for dogs under 1 year of age. Puppies receive 3 rounds of puppy vaccinations.

If you are interested in adopting one of our amazing dogs, please fill out our adoption application here http://bit.ly/PRAdoption and we will be in touch!

IF YOU ARE READING THIS, I AM AVAILABLE.

animal.description:
- Please visit our website for our adoption process & on-line application: www.crazypawsdogrescue.com
- Minimum adoption donation: $280.00
- Travel limit is 50 miles from the Albany Airport, no exceptions!
- A secure physical fence is required when children are in the home.

Hi my name is Hannah.  I have a happy personality, I love to snuggle, receive belly rubs and wrestle.  I'm about 1 year old and 60ish pounds.  My owner moved out and left me all alone to fend for myself.  We aren't sure how long I was living alone, the important thing is that life is behind me now.  I am loving having my foster mom around and my fur siblings.  Mom calls me an itch because sometimes I have trouble settling which is another word for saying I'm a busy girl.   I like to know what's going on in the house, so I'm up and down when there is movement, remember, I'm still a puppy.  My breed is a guess but I have some of the characteristic looks of a Ridgeback, the eye color,  the wrinkles on my head, my body color and the webbed feet.  The Boxer idea comes from the wrinkles on my head but mainly because I am all paws when I play.  In addition to being called an itch I also have the nickname of the bulldozer.  When mom moves I move right along with her, most of the time she doesn't move as fast as me and I bump into her.  She said if she fails it will be my fault.  I say she just needs to move faster......geez...  Me and little kids wouldn't be a good match, I hear they aren't very steady on their feet.  I love to snuggle after I'm done with my antics of boxing and nibbling on your hands, which mom says hurts so we are working on me not doing that.   I've been doing well not counter surfing but there isn't much for me to see there.  I did pull a towel off the counter that had some glasses drying on them, boy was mom mad.  I think that's a benefit, she has less glasses to wash and dry.  She tells me I'm like a cement block to move, I'm not a 6 lb lap dog....WHAT???  that's news to me.   I get to sleep with her but she struggles to get in bed because of course I want to be as close to her as I can get.  I hog her side of the king side bed.  I have no idea what personal space is with anyone and I love to give kisses, even to the other dogs.  I snore and sometimes I moan when I'm relaxed and sleeping.  I talk and play bow when I want attention usually with one of the other dogs.  I am a sweet girl who would love to have someone love me as much as I would love them.  Someone to explore life, teach me how to take nice long walks, not jump on you when I'm excited and not jump on the counter to help you cook.  No cats, no small dogs and no senior dogs because I do not know how big and powerful I am.   Apartment living is not for me I am too big and busy.  I am housebroken here but I use the dog door that I have access to all the time.  I am only crated when mom goes out which is not very often.  I would love a somewhat active person/family because I do get bored.  While I'm not high energy I'm no couch potato either.  I need some daily run time, walking is nice but it doesn't give a big happy girl like me enough exercise.  Living with a senior person wouldn't be in their best interest, remember my nickname of the bulldozer.  Please visit our website for our meet/greet/adoption process, www.crazypawsdogrescue.com          Love, Hannah

Age: 2.5 Weight: 85 Location: Philadelphia, PA Good with other dogs?: Yes, but is bossy to her foster brother. She is a bit dominant with him and tries to boss him. Luckily, he is super laidback and doesn't respond to her foolishness. Another dog might not be so patient. Good with cats? unknown, will not be adopted to a home with a cat Good with children? No young kids under at least 13 and up. Activity Preference: Needs a couple walks a day., Needs in-house activities, Up for a long hike any day. IQ: Smart Frankie's favorite things
Frankie is good at: meeting people, meeting dogs, staying in a crate, behaving in the house, going for car rides, walking on a leash Ideal home: someone at home most of the day, a fenced yard
Special Need: Frankie will take any chance she can get to eat any soft household items or toys. Her previous owners were very lucky that she always passed what she ate without the need for surgery. She has eaten towels, pillows, blankets, socks, clothes, soft toys. This is why she cannot even be alone with a dog bed and why we think a home without children would be safest for her.
Meet Frankie
Frankie is a sweet loving girl, 2.5 years old. She is house trained, crate trained and walks on a leash. She does well with normal commands (sit, stay, leave it) and sleeps in her bed at night through the night. She is playful, loves throwing her ball outside and going for walks. She's a big lap dog and loves to be pet or rubbed. She is such a loving, sweet girl and we want the very best home for her and for her future.

With Sadie's temperament we believe she would do great with kids of all ages but may need some lessons in manners. She has been spayed and brought up to date on vaccinations through the shelters spay neuter program.

Her adoption fee is $27.50 and she can be microchipped for $8.25. Due to the outbreak of Covid-19 our adoption policies have changed. All adoptions are by appointment only. animal.description:
This beautiful girl is Laiya! We bailed her out of the shelter the week of Christmas, after she was found as a stray & waited months to find her furever family. We know that special someone is just around the corner!

Laiya is a 5 year old Pitbull & her eyes tell it all; She is as loving as she looks & melts when you talk to her or show her any type of affection. She is a loyal companion that bonds heavy to her people & just wants that special person to give her the chance she deserves. Laiya does not prefer cats & would do best with a laid back, male dog or as an only pup so she can be spoiled like the diva she is! She loves going for car rides & is the most polite little copilot! Laiya is a sunbathing queen & will lay out in the sun as long as you let her; She would make a great travel or vacation buddy! She does get a little extra wiggly when she's excited, so older children that are more stable on their feet would be ideal! (Ages 5-6+) Otherwise, she smothers them with kisses! :)

Laiya is crate trained, house trained, spayed, microchipped, & up to date on vaccines. She is heartworm negative & ready to be loved in a home of her own!

To be considered for adoption, please complete an application below & we will contact you to schedule a meet & greet!

https://form.jotform.com/83106888643163

animal.description:
See below!*

Meet Francis! This handsome 5ish year old shepherd mix was rescued in Mexico and his back story is heartbreaking. A rescuer reached out to us with this message: “Good morning, they sent me these videos of this little dog who was abandoned with everything and his little blanket at the entrance of a place that sells crepes and hamburgers called sinful in Buenos Aires Sur, on Cucapah avenue ... they tell me that it has been there for days and He does not move at all from there, he looks very sad, if someone had the possibility to help him please.” We sent one of our rescuers to go get him and he is now enjoying the good life in his loving foster home. We don't know why Francis was abandoned on the streets- but we know he will know nothing but love for the rest of his days! Francis would do best in a home without cats as he likes to chase them, and can be a bit dominant with other dogs so a dog his size would best for a companion. He is so loving and grateful for every ounce of attention and every head scratch. Apply to adopt Francis today!


*Please kindly note: We do not respond to inquiries as we are a very small team! The submission of an application is the first step in our adoption process and is required to schedule a meeting, without exception. All of our dogs are housed in private foster homes. Please complete application below, and include any questions in the final section. We do not do out of state adoptions, and a homecheck, adoption interview, and adoption fee are required. For more information about our adoption process, please visit: https://www.muttscouts.org/adopt2 

https://fs6.formsite.com/themuttscouts/form5/index.html

Mutt Scouts is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit dog rescue dedicated to helping homeless, abused, and abandoned dogs. We are committed to providing proper socialization, training, and medical care for each animal we save, no matter the cost. 

Please visit our website for more information about our organization:
https://www.muttscouts.org/

animal.description:
Due to COVID-19 precautions, all animals for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. Copy and paste the link to access the sign-up genius for an appointment: https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet for dogs and https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1 for cats.

For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to elenahtar@gmail.com

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE:
http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Amos loves the beach! 
He is a very special dog. Amos is very sweet, loving and affectionate, tested so far with moms and teens. He's a short, stubby pup and very strong. He has a 1000 watt smile! And he must be young because his doggy breath is still sweet and clean - estimated age about 2 years. Despite his strength, he allows his humans to pick him up and put him in the bath, or lift him up onto the couch for a snuggle - his legs are a bit short for him to do it himself. He loves to snuggle and give slobbery kisses, lean on you and lie on your lap for head scratches and belly rubs. Amos is house trained and only does his business outside. He is crate trained and very quiet - he sleeps alone in his crate all night, quiet and dry until morning. Because Amos is completely blind, he spends most of his time being very quiet and listening to what is going on around him. Amos has no problem navigating despite his blindness. When Amos does sometimes bump into things, he takes it like a tank - he takes the hit, moves to one side, and keeps on going. With a little help from his person to alert him to stairs or guide him away from the street, Amos has no problem going for a walk to do his business, and can climb stairs easily (four or five observed). Amos is being treated for his heartworm diagnosis (treatment will be provided by HT and requires a rest period) so his walks are short currently. 
Being blind, Amos does get spooked by other dogs and it is recommended that he be an only dog, or that he go to a home where the other dog can be trained to leave Amos alone. 

Amos loves love! And seems to have no fear of people, only enthusiasm for everyone. He is very grateful for any attention then goes back in the crate when he needs to with no complaints. He is the perfect dog for an affectionate, patient person/family willing to help him figure out how to navigate a new home. 
Amos is heartworm positive. This requires some treatment that we will provide and a period of rest. 

Adoption Coordinator: Elena
Location: Foster Home

The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee INCLUDES spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program

animal.description:
Hi friends. My name is Watkins. Everyone keeps telling me what a cool dog I am!! 

My foster mom says I'm pretty close to perfect! I'm potty trained (so easy). I don't mind my crate (I'd rather sleep with my humans). I love all dogs (super easy). I'm great with people of all ages (sometimes a tiny human that walks on all 4 visits my foster mom and dad, I'm working on playing more gently with him).

I have a LOT of energy! As long as I am able to play hard and get my energy out I am a really good boy. I get into a little trouble when I am bored and have not gotten any exercise (I'm an adolescent, it's who I am).

I LOVE tennis balls! If I had my way I would just carry one around in my mouth all the time. After I chew them so long that I break them, I start to eat pieces and need them taken away because my foster mom says they might not be so good for me to eat. I'm ok with that, they seem to keep showing up when I need them. Sometimes I even throw them down the stairs so I can chase them when the humans are making dinner and can't throw it for me.

My perfect family is one that either has another dog I can run and play with, I like to wrestle pretty hard, or has enough time to make sure I get plenty of activity and exercise to keep being the amazing dog that I am!

Are you my people? I'd love to meet you. What type of adventures are we going to go on together?


--------------------------------------------


All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $450

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

Henry is a gorgeous two year old Husky/ White Swiss Shepard mix with beautiful blue eyes. He currently weighs around 65 pounds and looks the perfect image of good health. HE NEEDS A HOME WITH FEMALE DOGS ONLY, NO MALE DOGS.
However, Henry was found near death, malnourished and dehydrated about 6 months ago on Texas Star Golf Course. Trinity GAP arranged for him to go to our vet where he stayed for almost two months. Through it all he has remained one of the sweetest dogs you will ever meet. Henry just has a sweet soul. He is a very special dog to all of us who have been part of his long road to recovery. Henry loves people, children and other female dogs his own size. We are looking for a home with a single female large dog for Henry to live with. Henry loves to play with his dog sister, go for walks and snuggle. He is potty trained, walks well on a leash and has good dog manners. Henry is heartworm negative, neutered and totally vetted. He has been through so much in his young life, and we are determined to make sure he has a great home and family to love him. He will require a home with a 6' wooden fence. If you would like more information on Henry, please email wendee@sterlingtile.net

Hi everybody! I'm Red and I'm Hopper. We are super sweet Jindo mixes.  We know we get a bad rap sometimes but WE are VERY nice dogs. Everyone who meets us says so. We've been hanging at a used car lot for the last 7-8 years; ever since we were tiny pups. We've recently been set free and we are ready to take on the world together! Where one goes the other MUST go; we are bonded. We love to be outside but are really grooving on the inside soft bed situation, are very chill but if you want to go for a long walk or maybe a little jog, we are down for that too. Hopper needs to lose some pounds anyway. We were kept in a crate for 13 hours each day. We've only been off the car lot for one week and it's been GREAT! We've met a lot of dogs and no issues, we've gone for car rides and that's ok too. We have had no accidents in the apartment, we've been hiking ( so cool!) and we walk like the champs we are on the leash. Got checked out at the vet and had some shots.  Fecal and thyroid came back good. Hope to hear from you soon!

animal.description: Roxy is our official last rescue commitment of 2020 and we couldn't be more excited to have her with us! She is approximately 8 years old and went to her temporary foster home on 1/2. She needs all vetting and received her vaccinations today and tested hearworm negative...YAY!! We were told she is not spayed so we will get her pre-surgical bloodwork done and pending the results will get her scheduled for spay surgery and some dental work, too. Roxy is good with cats and with kids but can be dog friend selective. She is currenty in a temporary Illinois foster home but has a couple of long term/forever foster/adoption offers...she is a lucky girl!!! 1/14/21 UPDATE: Roxy was spayed today, had her teeth cleaned, had a few small bumps removed and was microchipped and she did great!!! She will be moving to her longer term/potentially forever foster in about a week or so.1/30/21 UPDATE: Roxy arrived at her Indiana foster home a little over a week ago and she is doing fantastic. She absolutely adores all of her foster skinbrothers and loves nothing more than being in the middle of all of their activities or just cuddling with them. Roxy will crate up like a dream and sleep in her crate all night with no accidents however she is struggling a little bit with getting her pottying outside routine down during the day. Foster mom and dad are working on that and have seen some improvement already!

animal.description:
This is Buddy. A Shepherd mix. He has beautiful eyes. Buddy is high energy. He will need a family that can help him burn some energy.  He is 2 years old. Buddy would benefit from some training classes. He's short on manners but when hot dog chunks used he all of a sudden can hear with those big ears of his. He loves going for walks but like I said needs to be taught everything. He's getting much better already. He needs discipline! He's eager to learn just no one has ever given him orders. I would not at this time think he should be with smaller children as he will knock them over. Children probably 12 and up would be best. A child who can take him on walks will become his best friend. All dogs can learn manners. He's smart and catches on quickly. A chunk of hot dog will get him in his crate and then I don't hear a peep out of him. He does his business outside. Buddy does NOT like cats at all. So definitely no cats. So if you have it in you to help Buddy become a great dog then you'll be fit for him. It'll take some time and patience, but he'll learn. He is neutered, UTD on shots, microchipped and has his rabies vaccine. Buddy's adoption fee is 300.00.   
Being fostered near Wisconsin Dells and Adams-Friendship. 

Update from foster 1/13/21 :
Buddy has come so far on learning. Most of his pent up energy is when he's coming out of his crate. He has learned that a door will not open for him if he's jumping up. He needs to sit, then the door will open and he's doing good. He has learned to sit, settle and lay down. He's even started playing with a tennis ball. Walks are getting better all the time. If he pulls, I stop, then he stops. Once he stops pulling he knows we'll continue our walk. This boy has a potential to be GREAT.

Update from Foster 1/19/21:
Buddy. A 2 year old Shep mix who's coat looks that of a chocolate lab. Buddy is neutered, UTD on shots, microchipped and has his rabies vaccine. Buddy is high energy meaning he loves to run and going for walks is his favorite. He does chase cats. I would recommend a home without any. Buddy is very playful with other dogs but because of his size I would recommend a home with a larger dog. Buddy is totally potty trained and keeps his crate clean and neat. He lays quietly in his crate. Older children are recommended. 12 years and older as he might knock a smaller child over just trying to play. He's learning to walk well on a leash but tends to pull now and then. His eyes are beautiful!! Buddy has learned alot in his foster home and continues to thrive. He's very treat motivated and loves to learn new things for treats  ? . Buddy would love to be in a home by Valentine's Day. He's not a barker unless he's telling you he needs to get outside. If you can be his Valentine apply to meet him. His adoption fee is 300.00.  He's being fostered near Adams-Friendship. Apply for Buddy at lastpawrescue.org 


Apply at lastpawrescue.org 
501(c) approved. Wisconsin agriculture number is 285589-DD

animal.description:
Pup Pup was one of five dogs surrendered by the same person to a crowded county shelter. The dogs had all been left outside, and neighbors complained about their barking. With this kind of start in life, it was no surprise that--upon his arrival at our shelter--Pup Pup had absolutely no idea how to walk on leash. But more importantly, he *did* know how to love and receive love from our volunteers. He's a sweet kid who had a rough start, but is ready for his second chance (INSIDE this time!) with a fun-loving family of his own.

Puppers is around 40 pounds and 1 1/2 years old (est birth 5/19). He spent the holidays on a trial visit with a prospective home. While he didn't turn out to be the right dog for them (and in particular, their skittish kitty), the family offers some great insight for future suitors:

"Pup Pup settled into the house very quickly once we brought him home. It seemed like he was probably used to living in a house since he only had one accident the first morning and let us know whenever he had to go outside. We had to keep him from getting into some things like the garbage can in the bathroom and Christmas tree ornaments, but other than that he seemed to be decently house trained. We'd have to coax him to go in his crate at night, but he did pretty well after crying the first few minutes. He also did very well on car rides, sitting patiently in the back seat.

"Pup Pup is a very active boy who plays hard and naps hard.  We tried to take him on at least one walk and play with him in the yard a couple times a day.  He really enjoyed playing fetch in the yard with me in the mornings before work, and quickly learned to sit before I threw the ball instead of jumping to get it out of my hand. He had no trouble at all keeping up on 3-mile walks, and still had plenty of energy to spare when we got back home. On the days when we weren't able to take him on as long a walk, he definitely seemed more restless and prone to mischief. We think that he would be happy in a home with another playful dog to help him meet his activity needs on top of regular walks."

If you think Pup Pup might be a good fit for your home, we'd love to hear from you! Please visit www.STAF.org to find out more about our adoption process.

•  All of our animals are spayed/neutered and current on shots.
•  We do not do same-day adoptions; we ask that you return for a follow-up visit before taking an animal home.
•  You must be 21 years or older to adopt from STAF.
•  We require a 4-foot-tall physical fence for homes with children under the age of 11. We also may require a physical fence for specific dogs on a case-by-case basis, depending on each dog’s behavior and exercise needs.
•  Due in part to increasing coyote activity/incidents in the area and the difficulty of predicting how a dog will respond to invisible fence training, we can not adopt to homes with invisible fences.
•  We do request vet and personal references.
•  We can facilitate adoptions within a 75-mile radius of our Cincinnati-based shelter.
animal.name: Pup Pup

animal.description:
Meet Bilbo!

Hello, the name is Bilbo. You know, just like Bilbo Baggins from Lord of the Rings, except I'm of the K9 species. I'm 8 years old and 60 pounds. I'm very kid friendly and there isn't a human that I've met that I don't love immediately. I enjoy cuddles and giving kisses. It's cold outside but I've been adjusting really well. I go potty outside and I'm not afraid to walk through some snow to find my spot. I also enjoy mind games and treat puzzles where I have to use my brain in order to get the treat inside. It helps to keep me occupied. I really like going on walks. It's like Biblo Baggins says, "I'm going on an adventure!" Maybe my foever human will like going on adventures with me. 

I really like to chase cats, so I don't think being in a home with them is a good idea, for me or them. I do really well with other dogs as long as they aren't in a crate when I'm around them, so when my foster mom leaves she puts me in a separate room. 
  I'm losing my hearing some, so I promise I don't just have selective hearing! You might just have to talk a bit louder. Sometimes you'll find me making a bed out of your clothes basket, and I'm not picky about the clothes inside of it being clean or dirty, I'm just looking for a nice, cozy place to lay that smells like my humans. Once I'm sleeping, I sleep hard, so you might have to touch me to wake me up. I sure look forward to meeting my forever family soon, and get used to their smells!

Albert's Dog Lounge is a transporting dog rescue, meaning that we rescue many of our dogs from high kill shelters in areas of dog overpopulation. We are a specialty rescue focusing primarily on senior and special needs dogs.  The vast majority of our dogs come from the Houston, TX area where we have an entire team of volunteers, coordinators, and fosters. We do also work with local shelters, rescues, and owners.  If you apply for a dog that is currently in our local Houston program, we will work to get your dog transported to WI as quickly as possible. We ask that you have patience during this time of uncertainty and unprecedented dog adoptions nationwide. 

Learn more about Albert's Dog Lounge, our mission, and adoption policies by visiting Albertsdoglounge.org. 

Our process includes an approved application, reference checks, a homevisit, and then a meet and greet with the dog. Adoption fee is $275.

Begin your application process by copying this link into your web browser: https://www.albertsdoglounge.org/apply

WI Dept. Of Agriculture License Number: 474085-DS

animal.description: This gorgeous Red Husky is looking for a forever home. Juno had been tied up in an alley for several weeks. Neighbors left food out for him, but no one knows who left him there or where he belonged. Finally, we were called to help. He was scanned and didn't have a chip or ID tag. We had Juno vaccinated, neutered and examined by our vet. He's a healthy young boy without any issues. He has a sweet friendly personality and has been fine walking on a leash and meeting other dogs on the street. Juno is very gentle, calmly takes food from your hand, and rides well in the car. For Husky lovers, Juno is the ideal dog! He would do best with someone who has had large breed dog experience. Like most Huskies, Juno will need a lot of exercise, so someone who jogs, hikes or likes to go on daily long walks is a must. Juno would love a nice, secure backyard to play. Juno is under 2 yrs old and weighs about 100 lbs. Juno has not shown any behavioral issues, but we still would not put any large breed dog in a home with very small children or cats. If you live in the Los Angeles area and would like to meet Juno, please complete our adoption application found on dexterfoundation.com Adoption donation $300

Meet Mack. This pup is almost 7 months old. He is a lab mix and weighs about 25 lbs. he won’t get much bigger.  He is a very special rescue as he overcame severe neglect and health odds to survive. Despite that, he is very sweet and loves humans and dogs. He is crate trained and learning manners. We will be looking for a home with a fenced yard or active adopter because he loves to run around and play. 

He was rescued after being abandoned in Puerto Rico. He was extremely sick and we spent months caring for him medically. He is finally healthy and ready for a special family that will love and adore him. He is available for adoption in Northern Virginia/DC/MD. We currently cannot do home visits in light of Covid-19 risks, so no homes with cats please since we cannot test whether they get along. 

Please apply at www.Project-SecondChance.org. Our adoption fee is $500. Review our adoption procedures on our website BEFORE reaching out to us. Check us out on Facebook or Instagram for more information about our rescues. 

FB: @projectsecondchanceforsatos

animal.description:
**WE ONLY DO HOME VISITS FOR ADOPTIONS NEAR BROWARD & PALM BEACH COUNTIES**

Check our New Years' baby, Rockwell ChiPoo (Chihuahua Poodle) He is lively and fun. He does take time to accept new people and will bark BUT baby talk works well to soothe him. He is 2 and a half years old and 10 pounds. He may not be totally hypoallergenic so if you have allergies to dogs, he won't be a match. Rockwell needs an adult home that will help him through his initial fear then he will give hugs to ask for attention. He comes around to love within an hour and he does NOT bite except at the vet when he is held down. Rockwell needs more work on socialization with new people. He does bark, so if you are in a high-rise situation where you would be passing people all the time and you are not experienced with how to help him overcome his fears, then Rockwell is not for you. He thinks he is going to be hurt so this may take a while for him to get over his fear. He is loving and cuddly once he trusts you but every new person, Rockwell will go through this fear until he is properly desensitized. You will need to continue with nonaggressive training in order for him to have a peaceful life and not incidents of him getting into danger! He is always following you around and instantly rolls over for belly rubs! He sleeps next to you as you with a subtle smile of appreciation. If you are looking for a little buddy, please check Rockwell! Rockwell's adoption fee is $350 to go towards his vetting (vaccines, spay/neuter, heartworm/Ehrlichia/Lyme test, fecal test, pre-op blood work, dental cleaning, and microchip as well as grooming if needed). If you are interested please fill out the adoption application For additional information regarding our adoption process, please check our FAQ's Page. 

 *All dogs in the care of Get a Life Pet Rescue live in loving foster homes while waiting for their perfect match. They don't live in cages or crates (unless there is a medical reason to do so.) They are treated as family pets while in our care. * All dogs in our care are fed premium brand holistic food as well as supplements and vitamins specific to each dog's needs. We don't buy inexpensive bulk dry kibble, our rescues are fed premium wet food diets as part of a comprehensive rehabilitation program to ensure maximum health.*All of our rescues receive complete quality vetting including full dental cleaning with pre-op bloodwork, spay/neuter, vaccines, and grooming. Dogs in need of specialized medicine will be seen by specialists, such as full cardiac workups, ophthalmologist visits, all suspicious lumps, and bumps are biopsied, and every medical need is transparent to potential adopters. *Once you adopt from Get a Life Pet Rescue, you become part of our compassionate family and we are here for you if a problem with your precious dog arises.

animal.description:
Perry is a nine month old, 85 pound St. Bernard mix that was turned into an emergency clinic after he was hit by a car. The owner had no money to do the surgery needed to repair his broken leg, so he was surrendered for euthanasia. Luckily the vet on duty did not want to do that and instead gave him pain meds, stabilized him and late into the evening started contacting rescue friends to see if anyone could take him by the time the clinic closed in the morning. It was the week of Thanksgiving and rescue was scarce, so it was ALR or nothing. We emailed x-rays to the surgeon we work with at Northlake at 11:00pm and his responded immediately that he could work him for surgery the next day!

The vet took him there herself and when the surgery was done, picked him up and has been fostering him. They have dogs, cats and kids and realized quickly that he was not very socialized. She has been taking him to the vet clinic when she works and he has gotten comfortable with people, but still reactive around other dogs. We are waiting for the surgeon to tell us that he can resume normal activities and then we will send him to our boarding facility and try to work him into our pack. A lot of times, reactivity in dogs is due to fear of the unknown. He has not had any experience with other dogs, so to him they are a threat. We just have to teach him that dogs are OK. Bottom line is that we are committed to cover the training that he needs to get over his fears. We are looking for an owner who will partner with us to guide him through this process. He is house trained and crate trained and a wonderful dog with tons of potential. If you would like to foster to adopt Perry, Please go to www.atlantalabrescue.com to fill out an application.

animal.description:
If you are interested in this dog, don't waste time with an inquiry! Fill out an application here to get the ball rolling...
https://pethavenmn.org/adopt/adoptable-dogs/dog-adoption-application/

Here is more about Diesel!

Nickname: Deezy
9-year-old, 60-pound Labrador mix

House-Trained: Deezy does great on a schedule and will usually give a verbal cue when he needs to go out. 

Crate-Trained: Does well – no blankets or towels in crate with him. 

Other Dogs: Does well with slow introductions and some time to get to know one another. Once he knows the other dog, he is very playful and would do well with a dog with a similar playstyle. Deezy is leash reactive, meaning he is vocal when he sees other dogs and pulls on his leash. 

Kids and Cats: We were told he did well with kids and cats prior to coming to Pet Haven. Would need slow introduction. 

Health: Deezy's allergies are looking much better and we should know more as time goes on. He would also benefit from a teeth cleaning. He is currently on GI prescribed food but may need to switch depending on allergy findings. He is also currently being treated for Lyme’s disease. 

Despite his old dog lumps and bumps (which are nothing to be worried about per his vets) Deezy is an incredibly sweet and loving dog. Vet techs and vets alike mentioned what a good dog he is and how polite and sweet he is! He is a great mix of snuggle bug and energy. He loves getting in a few walks every day, playing with rope toys, taking part in what his family is doing, and playing with his foster sister!

Patience with Deezy is key. That is how he builds his trust. Sweet Deezy came from a home that did not have time or resources for him have kids arrived and he found himself in his kennel more than any dog should have. He was rescued by a family member who intended to keep him forever until unfortunately, they found out they were severely allergic to him. He is now searching for his forever home that will be full of love, patience, routine and stability. 

Deezy is a bit of a barker and a vocal dog with whines and grumbles (in the MOST endearing way), and so apartment / shared-wall living is not an option for him. And while he would love a fenced yard for his golden years, it is not required. Deezy has benefitted greatly from slip leash training and this should be continued in his forever home. He is a wonderful, wonderful dog and truly an amazing companion. He deserves a loving home that will take care of him! 


His adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm/Lyme test, all age-appropriate vaccinations (distemper, rabies, & Bordetella), HW and flea/tick preventative, and microchip implant and registration. 

There is no guarantee of age and breed as a rescue animal's history is unknown. All ages and breeds are best guess.

Adoption fees INCLUDE a mandatory sales tax of 7.525%.

Due to post-adoption services provided, it is Pet Haven's policy to only place dogs into homes within a 75-mile radius of the Minneapolis, MN city center.

animal.description:
Raider is a one year old male pitty mix. He joined us in the rescue afraid of humans. He wouldn't make any eye contact with our volunteers and would just shake when they came around. He wouldn't even play with toys. After about 3 weeks of working with Raider, he finally started coming around and enjoying human contact and playing with toys (his bone is his favorite) . Once he learns to trust he loves to snuggle and give kisses. His favorite times of the day are breakfast and dinner. He LOVES his food. Raider would do best in a home as the only pet and without younger children. He has been fully vetted, up to date on all his vaccinations, neutered, and microchipped. The only thing left is finding Raiders forever home. 

His adoption fee is $150.00 which includes being up to date on vaccinations including rabies & bordetella, microchipped, dewormed, on flea/tick preventative and neutered.
We are a FOSTER based dog rescue therefore there isn't one central location with open hours to see our available dogs. They are all in loving foster homes enjoying learning how to be a furry family member. If interested we only set up meet and greets AFTER approving adoption applications with interested adopters as to not waste anyone's time.
All current/past pets MUST be up kept to date on vaccinations as well as being spayed/neutered to adopt from our rescue.

animal.description:
If you are interested in this dog, don't waste time with an inquiry! Fill out an application here to get the ball rolling...
https://pethavenmn.org/adopt/adoptable-dogs/dog-adoption-application/

Here is more about Woodrow!

Just under two-years-old (birthdate approx. 4/20/19), 100-pound Great Dane 

House-Trained: Yes, he will pace and go to the door when he needs to be let out. 

Crate-Trained: Yes, but he dislikes it and much prefers to be near people. 

Other Dogs: Has been attending doggy daycare and doing great! Has a more playful, puppy-like energy when meeting dogs one-on-one. He does best with medium to large dogs with a mellow and patient personality. 

Cats: Not Recommended

Kids: Woodrow is good with school-age kids and teens. 

Fenced Yard: A tall fenced yard would be great as he can easily leap over a standard fence, but otherwise he has been doing fine on a tie out when outside. 

Woodrow is a sweet and affectionate boy who loves to be around people and thinks that he is a lap dog. When cuddling, he will often lay his head on your chest. Otherwise, he will burrow his head under your arm. He has a magnetic and playful personality and enjoys playing fetch and tug. When playing or looking for attention, he has been known to occasionally jump with people his size but takes correction well. 

Woodrow loves to show his smarts and picks up new tricks and commands with ease. Along with continued training, daily exercise, physical and mental, is something he will need. He loves being around people and will lean in to being pet. We are recommending interactions with children under 13 be supervised and that he maintains mellow energy. He is a gentle giant but could accidentally hurt them during play or excitement. 

Woodrow would love to find a home where his human(s) are home most of the time and have large breed dog experience. He is a cuddly sweetheart who cannot wait to find his forever home!


His adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm/Lyme test, all age-appropriate vaccinations (distemper, rabies, & Bordetella), HW and flea/tick preventative, and microchip implant and registration. 

There is no guarantee of age and breed as a rescue animal's history is unknown. All ages and breeds are best guess.

Adoption fees INCLUDE a mandatory sales tax of 7.525%.

Due to post-adoption services provided, it is Pet Haven's policy to only place dogs into homes within a 75-mile radius of the Minneapolis, MN city center.

animal.description:
Foster location:  Boise ID 
Breed:  Blue Heeler
Age:  6
Size:  35 pounds
Adoption Fee:  $100.00
Spayed, Vaccinated

Adoption Application:  http://fuzzypawzrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application-2/


Pretty petite BJ came to Fuzzy Pawz after her owner passed away.  Poor thing got bounced around a bit before coming to us; she is unsure about what has happened to her old life.   BJ is shy but has shown she bonds deeply once she knows you.  

Once she trusts you she LOVES to cuddle with her person and be with them as much as possible.  BJ knows sit and will come when called; she is good on the leash and has a low energy level.  She’d love to have a new family that is home most of the time like her previous senior person was.  She cannot go to a home with kids under 15 as she has never been exposed to them and chaos/loud noises are not her thing.  BJ is house trained, treat motivated and would move the earth for her person.

BJ does not ride well in the car and gets quite anxious and is a flight risk until she is sure about her surroundings.  She will need to be kept on leash at all times when on walks, needs a secure 6’ fenced yard and her new family will need to be careful with her around open doors so she doesn’t spook and take off.

Due to some bad experiences in her past and not getting the opportunity to socialize with other dogs when she was young BJ is picky about other dogs around her and she is not good with small animals; she really needs to be the only animal in the home.   

Start off 2021 with a new best friend. BJ would love to have a new best friend to shower with love.

animal.description:
Dillinger is one big, happy goofball! Whoever let this bright and bubbly boy go is, quite frankly, a fool. Dillinger was found as a stray in a rural area who was so happy to be brought to safety. He's only about 3 years old and was taught some manners in his young life, but no one ever came looking for him. Dillinger is a little powerhouse! He sits and lays down when asked, and takes treats very gently, but he can use a bit of leash-training. He tries to restrain his excitement while out for a walk but he's just too darn happy! Dillinger loves checking things out, running and playing, and meeting new friends. He whines for attention like a little puppy and just loves people, but he'll need a home with older kids because he could inadvertently knock a small child over while playing. Dillinger seems to like larger dogs but needs a home with no small dogs or cats. He'll keep you laughing and bring you lots of happiness if you give him a chance! File#29908 12/5/20 Call 609-693-1900 or email: office@ahsppz.org to meet Dillinger.

If interested please visit our Forked River Shelter. We are open Mon. - Fri. from 12:00 P. M. - 6:00 P. M.; and Sat. & Sun. 12:00 P. M. - 5:00 P. M. for directions call 609-693-1900. There is an adoption donation required. The society cannot accept personal checks but we do accept Visa, MC, AE, Discover and cash. As part of our adoption process, we must have proof of residency. Homeowners must show proof of ownership; landlord approval is required for renters before an adoption can be approved.And as always we thank you for your kindness in opening your heart & home to a Society orphan.

animal.description: If Chihuahua's are your style then Moki is your guy. He is a classic Chi! He can be wary of strangers at first but he quickly warms up to you once he realizes you are a friend and not a foe. He'll let you know he likes you by leaning into your hand for pets. If a lap or leg is available then he will snuggle up against that. He will also give you a couple kisses if you ask him to. Moki is also a great guard dog! He will alert you to new sounds outside or inside the house. His mortal enemy is the roomba and the blender is a close second. He barks appropriately and only does so to warn you of any impending danger! Once the threat is eliminated he is a pretty chill guy. He spends most of his day sleeping on or near his favorite person. Currently he lives with 4 larger dogs and does great with all of their varying personalities. He tolerates his playful Husky sister, and leaves the grouchy and shy dogs alone. In his mind however he is the boss and size doesn't matter. He likes to be where the action is and his need for affection and attention takes precedence! He is a smart guy! He quickly learned the dog door and is house-trained. We do not know how he would behave around cats or children.

animal.description:
Back in the 80's, we loved the sitcom "Cheers". If you haven't heard of it, Google it and we would like to introduce you to our version of the character, Norm. Now, the looks are not even similar if you squint, but every time Norm entered the bar in the show, folks with erupt in a wave of hoots and yells. THAT is why our Norm is Norm. Your house will never be the same with Norm in it and every time a friend comes by, they will be unable to resist shouting "Norm!" and waiting to receive the hug and kisses that will always come in tow with this sweet and amazing and hilarious boy! Norm is about the cutest, wiggliest, funniest and biggest ham of a little Pittie boy who is about a year or so old and weighs aorund 40 lbs full grown. He is a face that cannot be described in words and an energy that is simply contagious. Norm cannot wait to find his own family who will love going lots of places and doing lots of things. He is big energy in a small package and would do best as a solo dog. He is quite the athlete and could likely keep up with anything you throw his way. Norm loves to do and play and is likely to be a best Velcro buddy with the face every mother could love. He is a good boy in his crate and likes to use the outside facilities. When your friends start calling and showing up at the door for visits more frequently, rest assured, they too have fallen in love with Norm as much as you have. Run, not walk, to meet this package of yum!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description: Ruthie is a very special lady to all of us here at Prairie Paws. She came in as a stray so we don't know much about the first 11 years of her life, but as we've gotten to know her in her 12th year, she has shown us that she is willing to learn a new way of life and gives thanks by showering you with kisses! 12 may sound like a big number, to Ruthie it's not about years under her belt but life experiences that's she's learned along the way, like how to walk well on a leash, and how to make someone fall in love with her, and how to use those big beautiful eyes to sucker you into giving her all the treats! When interacting with her, you wouldn't be able to tell that's she's a day over 2 because she's still just as playful as a puppy and just as eager to love you. She is hard of hearing, but the good news is you never have to worry about calling her to you, she's what we call a velcro dog- meaning she'll never leave your side, ESPECIALLY if you have some tasty treats. You know what they say, you lose one of your senses, and the others grow stronger. That's especially true for her, she can sniff out a treat from a mile away! Lately we've noticed that Ruthie has been sniffing around a lot, we think she's sniffing out her new family. Give us a call so we can set up a time for you to meet Ruthie and find out if you're the family she's been sniffing around for!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Clay County Animal Rescue & Shelter is located at 14400 Hwy. 45 in Louisville, IL. Our phone number is 618-665-3005. The shelter is open to the public 1-3 Monday-Saturday. Sundays we are open 1-4 to the public. If those times don't work, please call to set up a time to visit.

The typical adoption fee for dogs is $150. It includes vaccination, deworming , spay/neuter, heartworm testing on dogs of age and microchipping, which is now mandatory by state law. Some dogs we discount to as little as $50 due to sponsorship. Some dogs we ask a higher adoption fee, which helps us recoup expenses on heartworm treatment on other dogs.

All cats are spayed/neutered/vaccinated/flea treated/dewormed and microchipped prior to adoption. Cat adoption fees range from $60-$100. We spay/neuter/microchip/vaccinate and deworm all kittens and cats, prior to adoption. Our shyer/less adoptable cats are classed as "barn cats" and are free with a completed/approved barn cat application, which can be found on our website.

For updates on adoption events and more pics of pets available, go to our website, www.claycountyshelter.com or look for us on Facebook.

animal.description:
Gizmo is a handsome young Shepherd believed to be between 1.5 - 2 years of age. We know very little about Gizmo's history as he was owner surrendered to a rural shelter with no reason given. We do know that he was living on a rural farm and that is where he was raised.

Gizmo is a big boy and generally does okay meeting new people on leash. He can be vocal when he spots a new person from his crate or the yard though and has a very big bark. He isn't sure about visitors and requires guidance on how he is supposed to greet new people. Gizmo has been quick to warm up to everyone he has met and once he knows someone he is always happy to see them again. Gizmo is learning to ask for affection and really loves having one on one pets and cuddling. He can be more reserved if there are other dogs around getting attention as he generally defers to them. Gizmo has a very sweet, kind demeanor when he is comfortable and is a very loving boy. Gizmo can be a rambunctious and rowdy boy though and enjoys playing with people he knows. He is still learning he can't jump on people to initiate play. Gizmo has not been around any children at this time.

Gizmo was surrendered with another dog and is currently living with other dogs without concern. He can be a rowdy boy but generally defers to whatever the other dogs are doing inside or in the yard. He is not a confident boy and prefers to be a follower if that is an option. Gizmo likes to romp with the other dogs in the yard but if no one is playing he will also entertain himself. Gizmo has been around dogs 35 + lbs and has NOT been tested with cats.

Gizmo is a sweet country dog that is looking for a home that will teach him how to be part of the family. If you're the home for Gizmo please email Tierhavenrescue@gmail.com for an adoption application or visit Tierhaven.rescuegroups.org for FAQs

animal.description:
Macadamia is a beautiful Sable German Shepherd estimated around 2 years of age. Macadamia was found as a stray therefore we do not know his history or background prior to arriving at the shelter.

Macadamia is a smart, goofy young guy who is still learning how to navigate the world and what is expected of him. Macadamia can be vocal meeting new people especially when he is behind a barrier - crate, fence, etc. He has done well when properly introduced on leash and is learning how to make new friends. Once Macadamia knows someone he shows himself to be a playful and rambunctious boy who wants to be in the middle of whatever the people are doing. Macadamia is absolutely obsessed with chasing the water hose and is slowly figuring out actual toys. Macadamia has not been introduced to any children and is not currently recommended for a home with kids under 13. Macadamia is a loving and close bonding boy who is going to require a home committed to his ongoing training and socialization.

Macadamia does live with other Shepherds currently but is heavily supervised in his interactions. He is not sure if he wants to make dog friends and he lacks any semblance of good social behavior with other dogs. Macadamia has been able to acclimate to sharing the yard with one other large, young Shepherd however he has had some scuffles. He is currently best suited as an only dog but it is absolutely critical he receive socialization with other dogs to help him overcome his behavior. Macadamia is NOT cat friendly.

Macadamia is a young Shepherd that is looking for guidance, patience, and structure in a home that will help him learn what is expected of him. If you're the home for Macadamia please email tierhavenrescue@gmail.com for an adoption application or visit Tierhaven.rescuegroups.org for FAQs

Meet Hank!! Hank is a six year old male Rottweiler mix who weighs around 50 pounds. He is fully vetted and ready for his forever home.

Hank is a friendly dog looking for a home that will allow him to shine. Hank had a sad past, but is looking to put it behind him. He prefers a home where he is the only dog so that he can receive all of the love. Hank is currently in a home that does not have children or cats so we do know how is with either.

If you are interested in adopting Hank please submit an inquiry directly with Greater Charlotte SPCA by visiting charlottespca.org/adopt.

***Because our rescue is composed entirely of volunteers and we require a home check for each of our adoptable pets prior to them going to their new homes, local applications will take precedence. We will accept out of town applications, but any family further than 60 miles from Charlotte is responsible for finding a representative of a rescue local to them that is willing to perform the home check. All out of town applicants will also have to be willing to drive to Charlotte to meet/pick up the pet as soon as the application is approved.***

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Thank you for considering adopting one of CARA's Special pets! To apply read about our adoption policies
here
to fill out an application.
Hello! My name is Cullen. I am a dreamy, sweet 3 year old Chow/Lab mix. I LOVE attention and am SO SUPER cuddly. I was rescued from animal control, where I was super scared and shy and once I was given the chance I totally showed my true SWEET colors!! I am just a mush looking for a sweet home, that's all! I do okay with medium sized female dogs. To see more animals for adoption, please visit the CARA Website

Our adoption fees are:
Dogs: $155
Cats: $95
Puppies under 4 months: $115 plus S/N Deposit: $100
Kittens under 4 months: $70 plus S/N Deposit: $100

All pets available for adoption have been spayed or neutered (unless under 4 months please read about our adoptions
here
), are current on vaccinations and preventatives, and micro-chipped. Cats have been tested and confirmed negative for Feline AIDS and Leukemia. Dogs have been tested for heartworm disease.

Our shelter is located at 42 Deep River Rd in Sanford and is open Tues, Thurs, & Fri from 3pm - 7pm & Sat from 10-2pm (other times available by appointment). CARA's adoption process and online application can be found at
http://www.cara-nc.org/info/adoption

Please call 919-774-9433, email adoptions@cara-nc.org, or visit www.cara-nc.org for information about this or other pets available for adoption.

If you would like to adopt me or any of my friends, please visit CARA to fill out an on-line application or e-mail us at adoptions@cara-nc.org.

Every animal that comes into the CARA program is here because one or more events occurred that led to this animal needing not only a home, but a person or family to love and protect them. Each animal has been loved and cared for by a small and determined group of people who want nothing more than to know each animal is safe for the rest of his or her life. Thank you for looking to adopt!

animal.description:
Funk is a handsome German Shepherd estimated around 4 years of age. Funk was a stray therefore we do not know his history prior to arriving at the shelter.

Funk is a big boy with a pretty goofy personality once you get to know him. Funk has done well meeting new people in his foster home however he can be more cautious meeting people while out and about. He does not appreciate being rushed and is not the sort of dog you run right up to and start petting. He appreciates having a chance to check out new people first and then deciding to ask for attention or not. Funk can be a big teddy bear with those he knows and has a very sweet personality once he warms up to someone. He is still a playful, energetic boy though and loves to romp in the yard. Funk is eager to please and thrives with clear guidance. Funk has not been around any children at this time and is currently not recommended for a home with children under 13 years of age.

Funk lives with other German Shepherds in his foster home and does great. He loves to play chase games and romp with the younger Shepherds in the yard. He does well minding his manners and respecting the boundaries other dogs. He seems comfortable navigating a variety of ages and personalities from inappropriately playful young Shepherds to grumpy seniors. Funk has not been around any dogs smaller than 35 - 40 lbs at this time and would not be recommended for a home with smaller dogs.

Funk is a beautiful guy who is looking for a home that will give him some guidance and love as he figures out where he fits in. If you're the home for Funk please email Tierhavenrescue@gmail.com for an adoption application or visit Tierhaven.rescuegroups.org for FAQs

animal.description:
Belle Waselle is an approximately 3 year old female beagle that weighs 
34 pounds.  Belle is an all around sweet girl with personality galore.  She loves to romp with her foster brothers and sisters. Belle can be mischievous in the sweetest way possible but can also enjoy a good nap next to you or entertain herself with a toy or bone. She has enjoyed playing in the snow and going for walks. Belle's fosters are working on her house manners and she is learning fast.  She isn't a huge fan of the crate but is coming around learning that it is an okay place to be.  She is house broken and is very open to training.
Belle Wasale is a bit skittish around loud noises and is cautious in new environments but she recovers nicely and quickly. Belle is always ready for ear scratching, pets and "Good, good Girl". 

Belle Waselle is up to date on shots and preventatives and is microchipped.    Her adoption fee is $250 plus any additional donation you feel appropriate.  Our adoption fee is set to a level to make adoptions happen.  They do not cover our costs. Thank you for your generosity and interest in our dogs!   

All dogs adopted locally through SGDR receive a free six-week session of obedience classes and a lifetime of behavior support through our Project REWARD program with trainer Charlotte Blake.

You must have an approved application before being able to visit a dog. Visit our website below for an adoption application https://www.snootygiggles.com/dog-application/

If you expect to leave the dog alone for long periods of time, please do not consider adopting a puppy.  Puppies need lots of attention and companionship.  Thanks.

All known information about the animal is listed above. We do our best to give accurate information, but most of our dogs are rescues and do not come with a known history.

animal.description:
IMPORTANT: Please do not do an inquiry through Petfinder, our volunteers do not have time to reply to the inquiries. Please visit our website to learn more about our adoption process at newhoperescue.org. 

This dog is being fostered with New Hope Dog Rescue (Saskatoon).  If you are interested in adopting please fill out an Adoption Application. Meet and greets are by appointment only and done so after an adoption application has been submitted. A successful applications will be contacted by the foster home to discuss further. We are volunteer run so please be patient.

Vallee is my name, I was born on November 11, 2020. I’m a happy pup with a smaller mom but my future size is unknown as I’m a mixed breed pup. 

I’m working hard on life expectations with a foster home who is getting me on the right track learning all things puppies need to learn. My new family will need to keep it up  so I can perfect what I’m learning. I am doing well with house training, although I do need to be taken out on a regular basis. 

My favorite thing in life is to climb on my foster parents all the way up to their face and get snuggles. Anyone who will hold me and love me I adore. I like little kids around but really do enjoy my adult cuddles and being around people. I am learning right and wrong from my two foster siblings and they are fun to be around. I think it would be great to have a dog sibling in my new home. I can’t wait to meet you, if you would welcome me into your arms I will be a loyal friend. I am fully vet checked, first shots, and microchipped. 

Vallee has been microchipped, dewormed, current on age appropriate vaccines and has received a health check from a vet. adoption fee is $495 (200 is refunded upon proof of spay).

To view more dogs go to http://www.newhoperescue.org/adopt/available-dogs/

Disclaimer: in most cases we are guessing the breed mix. These are best guesses on our part. For puppies it can be extremely difficult and we are also guessing on what size they will be. 

NEW HOPE DOG RESCUE is not a shelter. Our dogs are placed in loving foster homes. WE NEED FOSTER HOMES TO HELP MORE DOGS - CONTACT US TODAY!!!
Definitions:
Pending - means that we are working through the adoption process with the 1st applicant. We usually don't add the pending until we are pretty sure the adoption will go through (like at the home visit stage)
Adopted - you know!! A happy ending for a homeless dog.

animal.description:
Evie, is a beautiful, loving, people-oriented, girl looking for a family who will make her the center of attention!  We believe her breed to be a Black Lab – Boxer Mix.  She weighs about 65 lbs,  is about 3 years old, is very well behaved (we sent her through a structured training program with a professional trainer),  and is an overall sweet, amazing,  girl. 
 
Evie loves being with people and will follow you wherever you go;  she is not fond of being left alone.  She listens very well, is professionally trained, and aims to please.  She loves to play tug of war and ball, retrieving a tennis ball when thrown.  However she will tear apart soft toys (probably to get the squeaker out…as dogs often do!!).  Evie also greatly enjoys going for long walks. And, walks very well on leash.
 
We feel Evie will excel in a home in which someone is home most of the time (including during non-COVID times), a family absolutely committed to providing her the love and attention she deserves.
 
An ideal home for Evie is one with solid dog experience, particular with larger breed dogs. Another calm but playful dog might be good for Evie,  but she would do very well as an only dog.  Evie would love a secure fenced yard to run and play, and definitely a comfy chair to cuddle and nap.
 
We feel Evie would do best with children over the age of 10 simply due to her size and playfulness!
 
BAARK Dog Rescue is based in Barrington, Illinois, and adopts only locally, that is, within 25 miles of our location. If you are interested in applying for adopt Evie, please contact  BAARKDogRescue@gmail.com or 847-852-0895 for an application

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Lakota! I came to MVPC from an Atlanta shelter because they were out of room and I was heartworm positive. It’s hard to go through treatment for that at the shelter, so I was lucky to come here with a few dogs! I successfully completed my treatment and am finally ready to find a forever home! I am a sweet, happy guy that gets along with people, dogs and even cats!  I am stunning with my bright eyes and shiny coat, and can totally rock a coat or jammies. I am active and now that I can get outside, I really like to! Toys and bones are awesome too! I used to get very nervous in the crate, but I am getting better and better now that I can get a little more exercise. But truly, I just want to be with you, whether on a walk or snugging in for a movie!

ADOPTION FEE: $200 (All MVPC dogs are heartworm-tested, completely vetted, spayed/neutered, microchipped, crate-trained and house-trained).

A $100 hold fee is required for approved applications and will be applied to the full adoption fee at the time of the home visit. 
ADOPTER: Dog experience 
BIRTHDAY: Estimated 2 years
FENCE: Required (an electric fence is not an acceptable form of containment)
DOGS: Yes
CATS: Yes
KIDS: Yes, over 5

INQUIRIES: ALL inquiries begin with a submitted adoption application, which is found on our website, www.miamivalleypitcrew.com. We do not adopt to individuals under the age of 25. We prefer male/female dog pairings unless both already reside in the home. 

DO NOT: USE THE PETFINDER CONTACT/ADOPT BUTTONS--we are unable to monitor those and you will not receive a response. 

PLEASE NOTE: We are volunteer based and a home visit is required; we have a two-hour adoption radius from Kettering, OH for our adult dogs and 75 miles for our puppies. Exceptions for our ADULT dogs only, though rare, may be made on a case-by-case basis but we must be able to do a home visit. Thank you for your understanding!

Professional Valentine’s Day pictures courtesy of the talented Gwen Estep Photography, Inc. https://www.facebook.com/GwenEstepPhotography/

animal.description:
Rosie is an 8 year old basset/border collie/shepherd mix, to the best of our knowledge. She was reluctantly given up by her family, when they had to move.  If you are looking for that special someone that is house trained, crate trained, loves to go for walks, and does well with both baths and nail trims (once she gets used to you), then Rosie is your gal!  Rosie only uses her crate to take a nap in now, at her foster home. She does well with submissive older dogs. She is good with cats and kids that are dog savvy. Rosie does prefer to dine alone. Rosie is not a huge fan of car rides. Rosie will need another calm dog that respects her space in her forever home as well as a physically fenced in yard for her adoption requirements.  She is being fostered in Parish, NY with cats and dogs. Her adoption fee is $200. 

If you would like to be considered for adoption, please submit an application: https://nybasset.org/basset-hound-for-adoption/adoption-application/


Please consider making a donation towards our veterinary expenses: https://nybasset.org/make-a-donation/

All basset hound/dogs are up to date on vaccinations, altered, and placed on heart worm preventative prior to being adopted.

*Our P.O. Box is located in Buffalo. Our fosters are located throughout NY State.

To donate toward his/her care, to apply for adoption, or to see other homeless bassets in need please go to http://nybasset.org/

The first step in the adoption process is to fill out an adoption application which can be found at the above website listed at the top of the page under adoptions.

ABC Basset Hound Rescue is in need of foster homes in NY state. We use foster homes throughout the state of New York. To apply, please go to https://nybasset.org/foster/

Thank you for your interest in adopting a basset hound.

Hi Im June! Im a 2.5 year old pure bred Alaskan Malamute. Im an awesome girl who is spayed, microchipped, updated on rabies, distemper, treated for fleas, ticks, heartworm negative, on heartworm prevention and been treated for internal parasites.  Read below more key points about me!


-Affectionate, intelligent, loving, good with kids. Older children preferable, as she will knock down younger ones. 
-Likes to play catch/ball, and brings back most of the time.
-Loves toys and will play
-Active home preferable. She loves biking with Springer attachment, we have also brought her scooter racing: she's strong and fast. --Think she would love bikejoring, scootering, sledding, carting. 
-Will need a fenced yard
-She's dominant, and she could possibly live in home with a large dog her age, but would prefer to be an only. 
-Likes walks, she will pull at she's very strong, but walks well on Halti lead.
-Loves car rides, but gets sick on longer rides
-Knows sit, down, stay, come, wait, OK, "Where's your toy", No, Out, Away
-Will counter surf if not watching
-Does not like to be left alone, but is not destructive. Does not do well if put in crate while gone. 
-Friendly with every person she meets
-Super intelligent and wants to please

Contact the rescue for more information about me! Adoption fee is $300
